results.best_full_model_response:
The expression to evaluate is (-98.3097)^(-7).

First, recognize that a negative exponent means taking the reciprocal: (-98.3097)^(-7) = 1 / (-98.3097)^7.

Since the exponent 7 is odd, (-98.3097)^7 = - (98.3097)^7.

Thus, (-98.3097)^(-7) = 1 / [- (98.3097)^7] = -1 / (98.3097)^7.

Now, compute 98.3097^7.

98.3097^7 ≈ 8.879 × 10^13.

Therefore, -1 / (98.3097)^7 ≈ -1 / 8.879 × 10^13 ≈ -1.1264 × 10^(-14).

To 3 significant figures, -1.1264 × 10^(-14) rounds to -1.13 × 10^(-14).

<answer>-1.13e-14</answer>
